The Arunachal Pradesh government has blocked entry of foreigners to contain the virus, which has infected 100,000 people across the world and killed more than 3,000 people. Efforts to check the spread of coronavirus has hit Holi celebrations in India and even in Indian communities abroad. Meanwhile, the centre has decided not to let any foreign cruise ship to dock at Indian ports, news agency ANI reported.
